
Package: shell/bash/completion 
Version: 1.0.0
Provides: ~/.bash_completion.d/zotonic
Maintainer: Eric Pailleau <zotonic@crownedgrouse.com> 
Homepage: https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/
Description: Bash completion script for Zotonic launcher script
 
 Add path to `zotonic` script ({/path/to}/apps/zotonic_launcher/bin) to environment variable PATH.  
 Create a directory for your bash completion scripts :
 
 $> mkdir ~/.bash_completion.d/
 
 Then edit a file `~/.bash_completion` and add:

 ```
 for bcfile in ~/.bash_completion.d/* ; do
    . $bcfile
 done
 ```

 Finally, open a new shell or update current shell by doing :

 $> . ~/.bash_completion
